2](../../../bib/kjv/isa065.htm#002.md)<span id="ii.xvii-p145.1"></span>. 
“It is a commonplace in patristic literature that the Crucifixion was
prefigured by [Isa. lxv. 2](../../../bib/kjv/isa065.htm#002.md)<span
id="ii.xvii-p145.2"></span>.”  (Dr. C. Taylor, *Hermas and the Four
Gospels*, p. 49.)  Cf. Barnab. *Epist*. c. xii.; *Didache* xvi.; Justin
M. (*Apolog*. I. c. 35; *Tryph*. cc. 97, 114); Tertull. (*contra Jud*.
xii); Irenæ. IV. xxxiii. 12.

