12](../../../bib/kjv/psa074.htm#012.md)<span id="ii.xvii-p147.1"></span>. 
The passage does not refer to Palestine especially:  “in the midst of
the earth” is equivalent to “in the sight of all nations.”  Cf. *Orac.
Sibyll*. viii. 302:  “He shall spread out His hands, and span the whole
world,” quoted by Dr. Taylor, “The Teaching,” p. 103.

